JOHANNESBURG - The 9th edition of the Cool Ideas Cradle Mountain Trophy took place between the 14-15 April with over a thousand riders tackling distances from 75km, 45km to 25km. The picturesque route made its way through Maropeng in the heart of The Cradle of Humankind, at an elevation gain of 1291m. James Thompson was once again the fastest man over the 45 km route finishing in 1hour 40min 50 sec to end top after two days. Juan Pierre van der Merwe finished the second stage in 1hour 41min and 23seconds to finish second overall. eNCA